        <num>CCP 1454</num>
        <heading>1454.  Objections as to disqualification of officer; waiver</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1454.  Objections as to disqualification of officer; waiver
An objection to taking a deposition because of disqualification of the officer before whom it is to be taken is waived unless made before the taking of the deposition begins or as soon thereafter as the disqualification becomes known or could be discovered with reasonable diligence.</p>
        </content>
